as Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","2546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381137","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-18","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-06-18T12:50:56.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381137/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381137/answer","PQ 2547 Sir Soames.pdf","PQ 2547 Sir Soames.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - UK's Productivity Stats","UKSA Letter to Member - UK's Productivity Stats","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381137/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-15","Productivity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to improve the UK's productivity statistics.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","2547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381138","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-23","<p>The British Indian Ocean Territory remains a vital strategic asset for the UK and the US, and a key contributor to our broader bilateral defence relationship. We have consistently said that we want to see the US presence there continue. No decision has yet been made about whether to seek to revise the terms of the Exchange of Notes, but we will have in mind this continuing, shared strategic interest.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2015-06-23T14:00:25.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381138/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381138/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381138/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-15","British Indian Ocean Territory: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what plans his Department has to revise the terms of the 1966 Exchange of Notes concerning the Availability for Defence Purposes of the British Indian Ocean Territory.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","2380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381139","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-22","<p>Category D gaming machines are the only gambling product that children are permitted to play. Public tolerance for children and gambling is, quite rightly, very low. Therefore the case for increasing the stake and prizes would need to be extremely compelling to make me reconsider the current levels.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-06-22T16:26:45.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381139/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381139/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381139/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-15","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will take steps to increase the maximum payout for complex category D gaming machines.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","2422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381140","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-22","<p>I have no plans to allow B2 gaming machines in amusement arcades. In April 2014 the previous Government announced action which included £50 staking measures on B2 gaming machines in bookmakers which came into force in April 2015. I think we need to give time for these regulations to bed in before we consider further legislative options. I will also want to consult with a wide range of stakeholders on this issue before thinking about next steps.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-06-22T16:29:15.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381140/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381140/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381140/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-15","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will take steps to ensure that bookmakers operate B2 and B3 gaming machines on an equal basis with amusement arcades.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","2581"
