"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381186","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-18","<p /> <p>In February 2012 the Department for Work and Pensions published the report “Income Related Benefits: Estimates of Take-up in 2009-10”. The full report can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-18T15:08:17.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381186/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381186/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-15","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in the UK are not claiming what value of each benefit and pension entitlement; and what proportion of each benefit and pension entitlement is unclaimed.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381187","Department for Education","false","2015-06-18","<p>The number of full-time equivalent teaching assistants employed in state-funded schools in England is published each year in the ‘School Workforce in England’ statistical series available online at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-school-workforce" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-school-workforce</a></p><p>Statistics on the number of new teaching assistants employed each year in England, Lancashire and Hyndburn are not available in the requested format.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-06-18T10:20:20.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381187/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381187/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-06-15","Classroom Assistants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many new teaching assistants were employed in (a) England, (b) Lancashire and (c) Hyndburn constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","2492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381188","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-18","<p>Data is not collected on the average number of hours of purposeful activities delivered weekly at each Secure Training Centre (STC). Young people in STCs are required to be out of their room for 14 hours each day, and are required to participate in education or training courses for at least 25 hours per week and 5 hours of offending behaviour programmes.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-06-18T12:04:34.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381188/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381188/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-15","Secure Training Centres: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the average number of hours of purposeful activity delivered each week at each secure training centre in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","2482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381189","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-22","<p /> <p>Staff within Secure Training Centres (STCs) and Young Offender Institutions (YOIs) are required to undertake training programmes that provide them with an understanding of the needs of young people within the establishments (including young people with learning difficulties) and how these needs may affect their behaviour and communication.</p><p> </p><p>Data is not held centrally on the number of staff working in STCs and YOIs who are qualified to work specifically with young people with learning difficulties.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-06-22T12:22:31.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381189/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381189/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-15","Youth Custody: Learning Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of staff working in (a) secure training centres and (b) young offender institutions who are qualified to work with young people with learning difficulties.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","2506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381190","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-22","<p /> <p>The Secretary of State for Justice will visit all three sectors of the youth secure estate in due course.</p><p> </p><p>I have visited a number of youth custodial establishments in recent months, including Feltham and Cookham Wood Young Offenders Institutions, Medway Secure Training Centre and Lincolnshire Secure Children’s Home.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-06-22T12:17:36.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381190/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381190/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-15","Youth Custody","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on what date he last visited a (a) secure training centre, (b) young offender institution and (c) secure children's home.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","2507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381191","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-18","<p>The number of young offenders that participate in restorative justice processes is not collected centrally.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-06-18T12:07:54.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381191/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381191/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-15","Reparation by Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of young offenders who have taken part in restorative justice schemes in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","2483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381193","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-22","<p>This Government was elected with a mandate to reform and modernise the UK human rights framework.</p><p> </p><p>The UK has a proud tradition of respect for human rights which long pre-dates the Human Rights Act 1998. But the Human Rights Act opened the system to abuse, damaging the credibility of human rights.</p><p> </p><p>We will bring forward proposals for a British Bill of Rights, which will replace the Human Rights Act. Our Bill will protect fundamental human rights, but also prevent their abuse and restore some common sense to the system.</p><p> </p><p>Proposals are being developed at the moment and we will fully consult on them before introducing legislation.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2015-06-22T12:28:37.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381193/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381193/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-15","Bill of Rights: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he proposes to bring forward changes to the rights of children in the proposed British Bill of Rights.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","2383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381194","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-22","<p /> <p>We firmly believe that education and training are crucial to help young offenders turn their backs on crime and find employment on release from custody. A number of initiatives launched over the last year put increased focus on education and training in youth custody.</p><p> </p><p>Under the Turn Around To Work initiative, more than 20 high profile employers in London and Manchester offer tailored placements to provide young people in custody with the training and skills needed to gain employment and lead a life free from crime. As well as work shadowing, placements include mentoring and interview skills training.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, four resettlement consortia comprising partners from the custodial estate, youth offending teams and local authorities have been established to improve support for young people in the run up to and on release from custody, and help them reintegrate with society. In pilots this approach led to 30% more young people having education, training and employment placements arranged.</p><p> </p><p>From August this year, all youth custodial establishments will be required to deliver between 25 and 30 hours of education per week. New contracts for education providers in public sector Young Offender Institutions commenced in March 2015 provide an even greater focus on education and will see the number of hours of education available to young people more than double.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-06-22T12:07:40.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381194/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381194/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-15","Young Offenders: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to ensured children and young people in the secure estate have access to high quality training and employment programmes.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","2384"
