"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381200","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-22","<p>All women’s prisons now have embedded resettlement services. These are provided under contract by the Community Rehabilitation Companies which are required to make sure that their services are tailored to women’s specific needs.</p><p> </p><p>Two 25-bed open units were opened at HMP/ YOIs Styal and Drake Hall earlier this year. The units are situated outside of the perimeter fence and only thoroughly risk-assessed women offenders will be eligible to be located there, focusing on helping them into jobs and preparing them for release.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally a 34 bed unit has been opened within the perimeter of HMP/YOI Foston Hall and two units totalling 78 places are shortly to open within HMP/YOI Eastwood Park. These additional places will mean that future women offenders can be held closer to home and are intended to contribute to their successful resettlement.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-06-22T13:07:00.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381200/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381200/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-15","Prisoners: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many resettlement units for female offenders have been opened in each prison since October 2013; and what the capacity is of each such unit.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","2457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381201","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-23","<p>Large capital investment is planned for the GB electricity sector not only in the context of ageing plants, but upgrading network infrastructure, meeting decarbonisation objectives and maintaining security of supply. Between 2010 and 2013, we estimate over £45 billion private sector investment in electricity generation and networks. We have estimated further capital investment requirements to be up to £100bn between 2014 and 2020. We have not estimated the proportion of this investment that relates directly to replacing ageing plants.</p><p>For DECC’s most recent published estimates of the costs per MWh for a range of generation technologies, please refer to the levelised cost estimates published in the Electricity Generation Costs (December 2013) report which can be found at the link below.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/269888/131217_Electricity_Generation_costs_report_December_2013_Final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/269888/131217_Electricity_Generation_costs_report_December_2013_Final.pdf</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-23T14:30:07.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381201/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381201/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-15","Electricity Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the planned capital investment requirements are for the new generating capacity required to replace closing electricity plants; and what estimate she has made of the cost per Mwh of electricity generated by such plants in comparison with current electricity market prices.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","2433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381202","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-23","<p>Scottish &amp; Southern Energy (SSE) has announced that it will close its Ferrybridge coal-fired power station by 31 March 2016.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-23T13:19:31.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381202/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381202/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-15","Coal Fired Power Stations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what information her Department holds on UK coal plants that intend to cease operations before June 2016.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","2434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381203","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-23","<p>Under the CCS Commercialisation Programme, the Government is supporting the Peterhead and White Rose CCS projects to complete their detailed project designs. The companies involved are expected to make final investment decisions in late 2015, with Government taking a decision in the first quarter of 2016. Subject to final investment decisions, Government has made up to £1bn available to offset the capital cost of the projects and further support will be available through a tailored Contract for Difference.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-23T12:56:44.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381203/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381203/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-15","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what timetable she has set for the completion of the carbon capture and storage commercialisation competition; and what progress her Department has made towards the announcement of a contract for difference for carbon capture and storage.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","2423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381204","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-23","<p>Rates of the UK-only carbon price are published on page A105 of the 2013 Budget's Overview Of Tax And Legislation</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/207419/022_fb20013_ootlar.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/207419/022_fb20013_ootlar.pdf</a>).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Budget 2014 announced a cap of the CPS rate at £18 per tonne of carbon between 2016/17 until the end of the decade, as shown on page A109 of the 2014 Budget’s Overview Of Tax And Legislation <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/294190/OOTLAR_19_March_2014__1_.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/294190/OOTLAR_19_March_2014__1_.pdf</a>). Recent trends in the EU ETS carbon price can be found on the ICE Auction Platform’s Report Centre at <a href="https://www.theice.com/marketdata/reports/148" target="_blank">https://www.theice.com/marketdata/reports/148</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-23T13:33:05.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381204/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381204/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-15","Environment Protection: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the trends in the (a) EU energy trading system price for carbon and (b) all-in UK carbon price, including the carbon price floor, were in the last six months.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","2435"
