"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381206","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-23","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State has regular meetings with Cabinet colleagues on a variety of topics.</p><p>Details of meetings between Ministers and external organisations are published quarterly on the Departmental website at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-meeting-with-external-organisations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-meeting-with-external-organisations</a>.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","2436 ; 2437 ; 2438 ; 2439","2015-06-23T12:55:35.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381206/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381206/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-15","Environment Protection: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what discussions she has had with HM Treasury concerning the effect of the carbon price floor on UK energy security; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","2424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381207","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-23","<p>The Department’s Updated Emissions and Energy Projections published in 2014 includes an estimate for the total amount of available coal-fired electricity generation capacity in Great Britain:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368021/Updated_energy_and_emissions_projections2014.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368021/Updated_energy_and_emissions_projections2014.pdf</a>.</p><p>The relevant figures are:</p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2020</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2023</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Capacity – GW*</strong></p></td><td><p>16.0</p></td><td><p>10.8</p></td><td><p>8.8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>*DECC EEP reference case (2014) – Unabated coal capacity based on a scenario of average carbon intensity of electricity generation of 100g CO<sub>2</sub>/kWh in 2030</em></p><p>The position of individual plants is a matter for plant operators.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-23T13:21:54.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381207/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381207/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-15","Coal Fired Power Stations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what information her Department holds on which coal-fired power plants will be available for electricity generation in (a) 2017, (b) 2020 and (c) 2023; and what the generating capacity in mega watts will be for each plant in each of those years.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","2425"
