"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381271","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-22","<p /> <p>No exporters have taken such legal action against the Export Control Organisation in this timeframe.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-22T09:43:02.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381271/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381271/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381271/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-15","Exports: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, which exporters have taken legal action as a result of the Export Control Organisation's refusal to grant them an export licence since May 2010; when each licence was refused; what the intended country of destination was of each such licence; what type of licence was applied for; and what the outcome was of each such legal case.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","2573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381449","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-18","<p>The duration of monitoring required after decommissioning/well closure will be assessed on a site-by-site basis by the Environment Agency. The environmental permit requires the operator to have in place a closure and rehabilitation plan, which must be agreed with the Environment Agency before decommissioning begins. The operator will not be allowed to surrender their permit until the Environment Agency is satisfied that there is no-ongoing risk to the environment.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-18T16:25:42.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381449/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381449/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-15","Fracking: Monitoring","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what discussions her Department has had with the Environment Agency on post-abandonment monitoring of onshore shale gas wells; and what steps she plans to take to ensure a monitoring regime is in place.","false","Biography information for Lord Lilley","Hitchin and Harpenden","Mr Peter Lilley","900406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381821","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-18","<p>The agri-food sector is worth over £100bn and employs one in eight people. The food and drink manufacturing sector – largest in the UK - exported nearly £19bn last year, including chocolates to Belgium, pork to China and chillies to India.</p><p> </p><p>Supporting and encouraging businesses to take the opportunities that exporting presents is one of my Department’s top priorities. Officials are working with the industry and UKTI to develop a new Action Plan.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","900420 ; 900422","2015-06-18T15:26:06.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381821/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381821/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381821/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-15","Food: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps the Government plans to take to promote British food and drink exports.","false","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","900421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381990","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-18","<p>161 schemes are due to start construction this financial year: 2015/16. This is part of the Government’s £2.3 billion six-year programme that will better protect 300,000 homes.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2015-06-18T15:21:14.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381990/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/381990/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-15","Flood Control: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many flood defence schemes are planned to begin construction under the Government's six-year flood defence programme in 2015.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","900419"
